  1. Backend API Endpoint: Typically, a serverless function (like AWS Lambda, Vercel Serverless Function, etc.) or a dedicated backend server (Node.js, Python, etc.) that handles form submissions.

const [errors, setErrors] = useState<Record<string, string>>({}); const [touched, setTouched] = useState<Record<string, boolean>>({});

const validateField = (name: string, value: string) => { let error = ''; switch (name) { case 'name': if (!value) error = 'Name is required'; break; case 'email': if (!value) { error = 'Email is required'; } else if (!/^[A-Z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Z0-9.-]+.[A-Z]{2,}/i.test(value)) { error = 'Invalid email address'; } break; case 'lossType': if (!value) error = 'Please select a loss type'; break; case 'amount': if (!value) error = 'Amount is required'; else if (!/^\?[0-9,]+(.[0-9]{2})?$/.test(value)) error = 'Please enter a valid amount'; break; case 'message': if (!value) error = 'Please describe your case'; break; default: break; } return error; };

const handleBlur = (e: React.FocusEvent<HTMLInputElement | HTMLTextAreaElement | HTMLSelectElement>) => { const { name, value } = e.target; setTouched(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: true })); const error = validateField(name, value); setErrors(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: error })); };
